Note
- The initial monitor node (Mon0) has only "true" outgoing arcs in the DOT.
- Therefore no compatibility constraint of the form "Mon0 -> formula(pre_k)" should be generated.
- If such constraints appear, it points to a bug in the compatibility construction (likely using node formulas instead of arc labels, or wrong state mapping).
- We should fix this at the construction level (not by filtering/patching after the fact).
